**Section 7: Exemption for Alternative Fuel Vehicles from the Vehicular Volume Reduction Scheme**

Pursuant to the objective of promoting sustainable and environmentally-friendly transportation solutions, any vehicle utilizing alternative fuels, including but not limited to electric, hybrid, hydrogen, or biofuel, may apply for an exemption from the Vehicular Volume Reduction Scheme (VVRS) in Quezon City. To qualify for this exemption, vehicle owners must adhere to the following steps and requirements: 

(a) Submission of an application form to the Quezon City Department of Public Order and Safety (QCDPOS), along with evidence of the vehicle’s registration, ownership, and the type of alternative fuel utilized; 
(b) Provision of a certification from the Department of Energy confirming the vehicle’s compliance with alternative fuel standards as per Republic Act No. 9513 (Renewable Energy Act of 2008);
(c) Payment of a processing fee as determined by the City Treasurer's Office;
(d) Successful completion of an inspection by the QCDPOS to verify the operational status of the alternative fuel system;
(e) Issuance of an Exemption Certificate, valid for one calendar year, subject to renewal upon re-evaluation.

Failure to comply with the aforementioned requirements shall result in the denial of the exemption application. The QCDPOS retains the authority to revoke the exemption status if the vehicle is found to be non-compliant with the stipulated standards at any time.

